* --- Reset / Boot ---
lcomment E000 cold boot: SEI, SP=$04AF, init ports/SCI/RTC
lcomment E022 slave sync: wait TDRE, send $00, expect $01 back
lcomment E034 copy 24 bytes from FFB5 to RAM $0100 (int vector JMPs)
lcomment E045 clear NVRAM config: $7F &= $CF, $7E &= $7F
lcomment E086 warm boot: SP=$04AF, init system, JMP boot_menu_entry
lcomment E091 warm reset: kbd/LCD init + CLI + RTS
lcomment E099 SEI, kbd_timer_init, LCD init, slave cmd $02, status query
lcomment E0AB clear session/device flags, init buffers $01D5/$01EC/$0208
lcomment E0C9 SCI reinit, session init, send CR/LF to slave, main loop
lcomment E0D5 disable EOCI/RIE, set P22=1, RMCR=$04 (38400 baud)
lcomment E122 if cassette active: send $7B then $77 to slave
lcomment E143 delay loop: X=$01F4 (500), DEX until 0
lcomment E14A SEI, enable key wakeup (LCDCTL bit 4), SLP, CLI
lcomment E161 display date/time prompt, accept 6 hex fields
lcomment E1A7 RAM size detect: write/readback loop from $004E up
lcomment E1C4 set RTC Reg B SET bit, write 6 fields, clear SET
lcomment E1DB poll UIP clear in Reg A, read 6 RTC fields into buffer

* --- LCD ---
lcomment E23F send full screen buffer to LCD controllers via slave SCI
lcomment E28A send LCD command byte to slave: $11:A via sci_two_byte
lcomment E292 clear session_flags bit 0, call sci_post_transact
lcomment E298 restore X, A, B from stack and return
lcomment E29C send row of 24 bytes from [X] to slave LCD: $10:byte
lcomment E2B3 BREAK check: save regs, scan kbd, test PWSW; abort if off
lcomment E2CF clear screen: fill line buffer with spaces, init display
lcomment E2D4 char output: printable/LF(scroll)/CR(reset col)/ctrl(ignore)
lcomment E2EB scroll: flush line to LCD, refill buffer with spaces
lcomment E2F3 fill $0197 line buffer with 24 spaces ($20)
lcomment E311 load D=$0808, fall through to lcdctl_write (set C/D=1)
lcomment E314 interrupt-safe LCD control write (shadow regs $4F/$50)
lcomment E332 read back all LCD controller VRAM and forward to slave
lcomment E3DA send character to slave: $30 cmd + A:B via sci_two_byte

* --- SCI ---
lcomment E3EF disable RIE, set P22=1, wait TDRE, write TDR
lcomment E3F8 send A then B via sci_polled_transact
lcomment E403 set P22=1, send 0x46 header + data, wait ACK
lcomment E45A check $7C.7 and $7D bits 4+5 for abort
lcomment E466 send byte via SCI without waiting for response
lcomment E47C check $7A.2, may call sci_start_irq_xfer
lcomment E48E configure SCI baud rate from table at E4AB
lcomment E4BB init circular buffer pointers in control block
lcomment E4E8 clear/set $7A flags, send $45 raw, enable RIE
lcomment E4FA enable/disable SCI RIE session (send $40/$41 to slave)
lcomment E4FF enable/disable EOCI timer session
lcomment E559 end IRQ session: disable RIE, send $46, clear flags
lcomment E561 disable RIE, set P22=1, wait TDRE, send $46, wait ACK

* --- Serial ---
lcomment E586 read byte from SCI circular buffer with parity
lcomment E5DF serial write: check CTS/DSR flow control, then send
lcomment E5F5 bit-bang serial TX via output compare timing + LFSR parity

* --- Cassette SAVE ---
lcomment E690 CAS0: SAVE init: buf=$0324, cmd=$64, ch=$04, ctrl=cb_cas0
lcomment E6A5 CAS1: SAVE init: buf=$02D0, cmd=$24, ch=$02, ctrl=cb_cas1
lcomment E6B2 common SAVE init: build tape header (HD/R1/HX-2/filename/date)
lcomment E710 copy 16-byte filename from io_desc+3 into header+8
lcomment E735 set up header block transfer: 84 bytes
lcomment E75A init ctrl_block: buf ptrs, byte_count=$54

* --- Block Transfer ---
lcomment E777 start block xfer (SAVE): set $7A.7 (send mode), enable RIE
lcomment E78C send slave_cmd via sci_polled_transact, expect ACK=1
lcomment E7D7 enable RIE to start IRQ-driven data transfer
lcomment E7DA wait loop: poll RIE bit until IRQ handler clears it
lcomment E810 CAS0: buffered write, auto-flush when full
lcomment E81A CAS1: buffered write, auto-flush when full
lcomment E822 common write: verify mode, check errors, store byte, advance
lcomment E851 flush full buffer via block_xfer_start
lcomment E85F CAS0: close SAVE: flush + EOF + $7B+$77 cleanup
lcomment E86C CAS1: close SAVE: flush + EOF + close transact
lcomment E891 write EOF block: increment count, set "EOF " marker
lcomment E8D0 CAS1: SCI close command ($22 or $23)

* --- Cassette Read ---
lcomment E8E4 CAS0: read byte, cmd=$68, ch=$04, ctrl=cb_cas0
lcomment E8F2 CAS1: read byte, cmd=$28, ch=$02, ctrl=cb_cas1
lcomment E8FE common read: verify mode=$04, auto-load next block if empty
lcomment E948 CAS0: open for read with metadata copy
lcomment E95E CAS1: open for read with metadata copy
lcomment E96D common open-read: search tape for filename match
lcomment E97A init ctrl_block: clear counters, set buf ptrs, byte_count=$54
lcomment E9B3 compare 16-char filename, support '*' wildcard
lcomment E9F1 check file protection: header[$19] != space

* --- Transfer Setup ---
lcomment EA01 set up data block transfer: src_ptr, end_addr, byte_count
lcomment EA23 CAS0: LOAD first block (cmd=$66)
lcomment EA28 CAS0: LOAD retry (cmd=$67)
lcomment EA2D CAS0: LOAD next block (cmd=$68)
lcomment EA3E CAS1: LOAD first block (cmd=$26)
lcomment EA43 CAS1: LOAD retry (cmd=$27)
lcomment EA48 CAS1: LOAD next block (cmd=$28)
lcomment EA57 common LOAD: retry loop + wait for completion
lcomment EA77 wait: poll P12 (slave flag) and TRCSR RIE bit
lcomment EAB9 save status, clear session flags, sci_post_transact
lcomment EAD0 disable RIE, reset ptrs, send device cmd, enable RIE
lcomment EB0A redirect OCF vector to EF85, set debounce counter=9

* --- SAVE Protocol ---
lcomment EB16 send $50 status query, read PORT1, update $79
lcomment EB47 status query + check bit 2 (tape ready)
lcomment EB54 save_device_setup + send $7C (set device mode)
lcomment EB6F compute tape seek distance, send $72 or $73
lcomment EBA9 send $6D + tape position ($0203) via sci_two_byte
